The paper deals with image super-resolution using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of deep learning architectures, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with satellite and overhead imagery, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
